                "7fd64c17e2d3e69d66e6b90377764f95d27f5e6d"
            ],
            "ref": "refs/changes/19/36719/6",
            "uploader": {
                "name": "Jason Bills",
                "email": "jason.m.bills@linux.intel.com",
                "username": "jmbills"
            },
            "createdOn": 1611873976,
            "author": {
                "name": "Jason Bills",
                "email": "jason.m.bills@linux.intel.com",
                "username": "jmbills"
            },
            "kind": "TRIVIAL_REBASE",
            "comments": [
                {
                    "file": "include/error_monitors/smi_monitor.hpp",
                    "line": 46,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Richard Marian Thomaiyar",
                        "email": "richard.marian.thomaiyar@linux.intel.com",
                        "username": "rthomaiy"
                    },
                    "message": "With this logic, assert handler will be called more than once (i.e. After assertHandler(), polling will happen again, as assertHandler() is async operation, causing second assert to trigger the Crashdump (even before first one got a chance to complete right?).\nHow we are avoiding this? (Esp. in terms of SMI timeout)."
                },
                {
                    "file": "include/error_monitors/smi_monitor.hpp",
                    "line": 46,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Jason Bills",
                        "email": "jason.m.bills@linux.intel.com",
                        "username": "jmbills"
                    },
                    "message": "After assertHandler() is called, it switches back to waiting for the event and stops polling, so we shouldn't get a second assertHandler() call from a single timeout event."
                },
                {
                    "file": "include/error_monitors/smi_monitor.hpp",
                    "line": 46,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Richard Marian Thomaiyar",
                        "email": "richard.marian.thomaiyar@linux.intel.com",
                        "username": "rthomaiy"
                    },
                    "message": "assertHandler() --> will be started (not completed) and will go for waitForEvent(), but if event is received before assertHandler() completes, then assertHandler() will be called again, followed by waitForEvent() (even when the previous operation is not yet done)."
                },
                {
                    "file": "include/error_monitors/smi_monitor.hpp",
                    "line": 46,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Jason Bills",
                        "email": "jason.m.bills@linux.intel.com",
                        "username": "jmbills"
                    },
                    "message": "That's true, but the timeout is 90 seconds, so I don't expect multiple events to happen before the first returns.  I'm open to suggestions to fix it, if needed."
                }
            ],
            "files": [
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "type": "ADDED",
